<title>ARGENTINA: Argentina's Peronists defend Menem's labor reforms.</title>
<headline>Argentina's Peronists defend Menem's labor reforms.</headline>
<byline>Stephen Brown</byline>
<dateline>BUENOS AIRES 1996-09-02</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Argentine government Monday tried to counter criticisms of President Carlos Menem's proposals for more flexible labor laws, arguing that not just workers would contribute to new unemployment insurance.</p>
<p>Menem angered trade unions, already in disagreement over his fiscal austerity programmes, by announcing a labor reform package Friday including suspending collective wage deals and replacing redundancy payouts with unemployment insurance.</p>
